Here’s a compact `@media print` block you can append to your stylesheet so the browser automatically cleans up margins, colors, and page breaks when exporting to PDF or paper:

```css
@media print {
  @page {
    size: Letter;         /* or A4 */
    margin: 1.25in;
  }

  body {
    background: #fff !important;  /* white background for print */
    color: #222;
  }

  h2 {
    background-color: #ece8e1 !important; /* slightly darker tint */
    color: #333;
    page-break-after: avoid;
  }

  p {
    page-break-inside: avoid;
    orphans: 3;           /* keep at least 3 lines together */
    widows: 3;
  }

  hr {
    border-top: 1pt solid #bbb;
    margin: 14pt auto;
    width: 50%;
  }

  footer {
    position: running(footer);
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 9pt;
    color: #888;
    margin-top: 24pt;
  }

  /* optional: hide web-only elements such as nav bars */
  nav, .screen-only { display: none; }
}
```

This ensures each section remains whole on a single page and the soft tonal palette prints clearly.  
